1+\omega +\omega^2+\omega^3 -\frac{1}{\omega} \\
\end{vmatrix} =$$ My approach : $$\omega^5 = 1 \\ \implies 1+\omega +\omega^2 +\omega^3 + \omega^4 =0$$ Therefore, \begin{align}\log_2 |1+\omega +\omega^2+ \omega^3 -\frac{1}{\omega}| &=\log_2 |1+\omega +\omega^2+ \omega^3 -\omega^4|\\& =\log_2|-2\omega^4|\\ &=\log_2 2 +\log_2 \omega^4 \end{align} Now how to solve further; please suggest.
